(1142, 11, 'Diggi Palace', 'Diggi House, Sawai Ram Singh Road, C-Scheme, Shivaji Marg , Opp SMS hospital', '|Diggi Palace was built in 1860 and for many years it served as the residence of a royal family. The property was later converted into a hotel but it still retains its old world charm. Exquisite architecture, state-of-the-art facilities and warm hospitality are the highlights of this property. Services offered here include laundry, currency exchange and doctor-on-call.| To make the stay comfortable for guests, the hotel offers facilities like gymnasium, internet centre, spa, swimming pool, library are offered here. At leisure, guests can avail Kerala Ayurvedic massages, attend yoga classes or go for rural excursions, jeep safari, folk dances and golf. The hotel also organises cultural events and cookery workshops for guests. For business guests, the property features a conference hall, which is provided with all essential facilities.| This luxury property offers 70 well furnished rooms, which are available in different categories, namely Heritage Room, Palace Suite and Courtyard Suite. Amenities like cable TV, tea/coffee maker, telephone, television with cable connection and internet are provided in all rooms. Attached bathrooms feature modern toiletries and 24-hour water supply.| Featuring stunning decor, comfortable seating arrangement and exquisite light fittings, the in-house restaurant, named The Baradari Mahal, delights guests with lip-smacking dishes. For those who wish to savour authentic Rajasthani fare, this place is excellent.| While staying here, guests can plan a visit to Hawa Mahal, which is just a 9-minute drive from here.| |less', 8739, 4.0, 5.0, 5.0),
