(1480, 36, 'Shahi Niwas', 'Maruti Crossing, Andhrapul GT Road Varnasi', 'Situated in the city that attracts countless pilgrims, also known as City of Moksha, Varanasi, Shahi Niwas is a classic property that offers reliable accommodation, warm hospitality, personalized services and modern facilities in the enchanting city. This value for money property that offers a convenient location to business and leisure travellers. The warm and supportive staff ensures any and every whim is met at the earliest. The nearest airport and railway station to the region is Lal Bahadur Shastri International Airport and Varanasi Railway Station. Quietly elegant and exclusive the property facilitates services like front desk and many more that provides a comfortable and tranquil stay to guests. The rooms of the hotel are sumptuous, elegantly designed with cosy interiors and also come with comfy beds and good quality linens. To ease the stress of travel, the hotel offers necessary room amenities that satisfy the needs of the most discerning guests. Well maintained bathrooms here are fitted with essential bathroom amenities and toiletries. Have a relaxed stay at Shahi Niwas!', 6256, 5.0, 5.0, 5.0),
(1481, 36, 'Hotel Ishan Paying Guest House', 'B-1/150,1D1, Jagarnath Gali Lodging Street Assi, Varanasi Assi Ghat', 'Hotel Ishan Paying Guest House is a 2 star property, located at an accessible distance from Airport, Railway Station and Bus Station. The property is a a family run guest house that is preferable choice for travellers visiting the holy city. It has air-conditioned and non-air-conditioned rooms that feature all comforts of a home. Amenities provided in room include standard facilities and attached bathroom with running hot and cold water. For convenience of guests, Wi-Fi and 24-hour room service is provided. Besides spacious rooms, the guest house boasts of a yoga facility on the rooftop that gives guests a chance to uplift their senses in the sacred environs of Varanasi. Upon request, the guest house also offers pick up and drop facility to guests and makes boating arrangements. There is a shared kitchen within the guest house where guests can cook their own food, as and when required. Those who do not wish to cook can explore the eateries around the place that serve good food. Guests can find some must visit areas of attraction, which are closed to the property like Assi Ghat (500 metres), Durga Temple (1.2 kms) and Kashi Vishwanath Temple (4.2 kms). Climb the rooftop to behold unobstructed views of the sacred Ganges!', 6424, 4.0, 4.0, 4.0),
