(2348, 111, 'Shahpura Bagh - 50KM away from Bhilwara', 'Shahpura District Bhilwara ,', '|Enveloped in verdant green plains, lotus covered pond and beautiful architecture of a heritage fort, Shahpura Bagh is an oasis of natural grandeur. Legend has it that, in the 1920\'s, Rajadhiraj Nahar Singh of Shahpura mortgaged the family\'s private property and jewels to bring water to his people. Today, the three lakes he created, Nahar Sagar, Umaid Sagar and the Arvardh Dam, along with 250 small lakes form the heart of a verdant wetland refuge - historic, picturesque, tranquil - an idyllic setting where man and nature have come to understand each other. The Shahpura Bagh is located at Shahpura, District Bhilwara in Rajasthan, about 200 kilometres away from Sawai Madhopur, 220 kilometres from the Jaipur airport and 50 kilometres away from the Bhilwara railway station. |Hotel Facilities| The heritage resort has a shop selling local souvenirs and clothes. There is an activity centre as well, which houses a television and various indoor games. Those interested, can take a walk in the walled bio-vegetable garden of the fort. Besides this, guests can go on sightseeing excursions and outdoor activities like wildlife picnics, boat ride, safaris and bird watching treks. There is a travel desk here as well and a banquet hall where parties and weddings can be arranged. |Room Amenities| The rooms are warm and gracious and offer traditional hospitality. The 5 beautifully appointed Suites and 4 Double rooms with en-suite bathrooms; all combine to make the Bagh a perfect retreat with amenities like world space radio, coffee and tea makers, hair dryers, EPABX and phone as well as Biotique herbal toiletries. |Dining| Guests can take their pick from authentic home cooked Rajasthani food prepared over fire or home-cooked continental and tradition meals. Guests can enjoy the delicious cuisines with their choice of seating, in the heritage dining hall or out in the sprawling lawns. Internet: Not