(3072, 318, 'Desert Springs Resort', 'Kanoi Village, Sam Dunes Jaisalmer', 'Jaisalmer was a preferred trade route in the past. Tracing this route again is a nostalgic experience waiting for your presence. We have recreated the magic of this route and combined it with the cultural infusion of music, dance and food.Upon your arrival you are welcomed in a typical rajathanimanner. Then you are whisked away to watch the spectacular colours of the sunset sky on the camel back. After Camel Safari you can unwind in the late evening hours on maharaja style sitting arrangement whereby traditional musicians and dancers will enthral you with their colourful and soulful Rajasthani folk music &Kalbelia dance. A sumptuous dinner follows and you can have a good night\'s sleep under the quite starry sky. Enjoy the desert experience like a true RajasthaniRoyal ! Chanani \\\"Light of Moon\\\" - The highlight of your stay with us is our cultural program combined with dine-in experience called \'Chanani\'. The \'Light of the Moon\' will embrace you with its soft light and mesmerising calmness. Feel the romance of the desert in open starlit sky with the colourful dances and folk songs that gives you goose bumps! The desert air surely resonates with the renderings of soulful music to the dance beats in rhythmic swirls.Dindhhle \\\"The Sunset Bar\\\"-Our bar Ãƒ?Ã†??????Ãƒ?Ã†?????????DindhhleÃƒ?Ã†??????Ãƒ?Ã†????????? is aptly named because Ãƒ?Ã†??????Ãƒ?Ã†?????????SunsetÃƒ?Ã†??????Ãƒ?Ã†????????? time is the perfect time for all folks to unwind. Dindhhlestocks all kinds of liquors and alcoholic drinks as well as mixed beverages. We understand that you need to chill out and relax and what better way to unwind and wash down all the worries of the world in a glass?Charkho \\\"Salty & Spicy\\\" - We have built a restaurant within the colony premises. Our restaurant Ãƒ?Ã†??????Ãƒ?Ã†?????????CharkoÃƒ?Ã†??????Ãƒ?Ã†????????? gives the right balance of salty and spicy flavours. Charkocaters to your taste buds with a range of cuisines from continental to Chinese. Our menu has all the food items available at any time of the day.Baithak \\\"The Conference Hall\\\"- We have created a Conference Hall too for those professional sit outs. When you have to combine your tours with business purposes; our conference Hall \'Baithak\' gives you the right discussion group advantage complete with all amenities that a conference room provides. Who said one cannot do business in middle of the desert?Teelo \\\"The Camel Ride Point\\\"- No rendezvous with Rajasthan is complete without the camel ride; especially in Jaisalmer. The picturesque setting of the sand dunes, sunset and the camel silhouette is a visual delight. You get to soak into this nostalgic imagery at our camel point \'Tillo\'. It is here that you get to experience the vastness of the desert and also get to know the way of life. On the camel back, soak in the natural beauty of the vast expanse and breathe in the desert; you\'ll realise that time stands still in this magical place where hot days merge with cold nights.There is great value in being able to say \\\"yes\\\" when people ask if there is anything we can do. By letting people allow us to make them feel good, we are making up a world of happy people. The more environments with that atmospheric makeup we can find or create, the better.This is what keeps Priya Group going ahead and surging forward.', 6946, 4.0, 4.0, 4.0),
(3073, 318, 'Hotel Jeet Mahal', 'Near Fort Gate, Aasni Road Aasni Road', 'Located within 2.6 km radius from Jaisalmer Railway Station, Hotel Jeet Mahal, has a restaurant, Wi-Fi connectivity and Ayurvedic massage. Hotel Jeet Mahal is an 18th century property that is located within 8 minutes drive from the Jaisalmer Railway Station. Popular tourist attractions like Amar Sagar Lake and Patwon ki Haveli are easily accessible from the hotel. It has 6 beautifully designed rooms that are provided with amenities like air-conditioner, cable TV and telephone. For the convenience of business as well as leisure guests, the hotel offers facilities like Cyber Cafe-cum-bar, laundry, travel assistance and ticket booking. After a tiring day, guests can enjoy Ayurvedic massages offered at the hotel. Upon request, arrangements for camel rides and folk dances are also made. The hotel has an in-house restaurant, which serves many vegetarian Indian dishes. Further, there is a cyber cafe-cum-bar, where guests can relish delightful drinks with their friends. Jaisalmer Fort, an epitome of architectural excellence, lies close to the hotel.', 4546, 5.0, 4.0, 4.0),
(3074, 318, 'Hotel Sona', 'Mohangarh Rd, Amar Sagar Pol, Jaisalmer, Rajasthan', '', 7049, 5.0, 5.0, 4.0),
(3075, 318, 'Hotel Desert Tulip', '4 Hotel Complex, Jodhpur Road (NH15) Hotel Complex', 'Hotel Desert Tulip is a 3 star hotel, located at 5.8 kms from Jaisalrmer airport, 3.6 kms from Jaisalmer Railway Station and 3.3 kms from Jaisalmer Main bus Stop. Desert Tulip Hotel and Resort stands as an oasis of warmth and hospitality in the heart of the enigmatic Thar. A towering sandstone wonder synonymous with romance, chivalry, culture and beauty. The hotel embraces intricate carvings on the yellow sand stone made by the local craftsmen, blending tradition with contemporary elegance. Hotel facilities include business center, conference hall, babysitting service, handicap facility, gymnasium, Wi-Fi enabled, bar, taxi services, travel desk, railway station transfer, doctor on call, laundry and lawns/gardens. Recreational services include swimming pool, kids pool, activity center, beach beds, sun beds pool, games room, health club, massage center, outdoor activities, ayurveda center, spa and executive lounge. Chargeable services include airport transfer, guide service and sightseeing. In room amenities include air conditioning, living room, television, intercom, direct dial phone, Wi-Fi internet (Chargeable), snack basket (Chargeable), fruit basket (Chargeable), mini bar, tea/coffee maker, mineral water, refrigerator, iron and ironing board (On Request), balcony/sit out, dinning table, sofa unit (Mini Suite), study table, daily newspaper, safe deposit locker, electronic safe, room heater (On Request), shower area, bath tub, hot/cold water and bathroom toiletries. Desert Tulip Hotel and Resort houses 2 multi cuisine restaurants, Ciro and Mehraab, and Saanjh Â? The Bar. Mouth watering cuisines, from the native land blend well on the palate. For a truly remarkable dining experience, enjoy Mehraab, the rooftop restaurant with a breathtaking view of the Jaisalmer Fort and picturesque sunsets. Open Air Bar-be-que with bonfire and traditional entertainment will capture your evening. Tantalizing assortment of dessert on our well laden buffet or a-la-carte menu is the best way to end your day. The hotel offers banquets which can accommodate 250 people easily and offer the perfect setting for any kind of events. The hotel also have a conference room equipped with the best of modern facilities for your business meetings. Guests can access your office even when they are away from it. The business center gives all work related services along with Wi-Fi Internet facility. Experience a Grand stay and warm experience at Hotel Desert Tulip!', 4190, 5.0, 4.0, 5.0),
(3076, 318, 'Desert Safariors Camps', 'Sam Sand Dunes Jaisalmer', 'Nestled among the enthralling sand dunes. Desert Safariors Camps is located at a distance of 28.6 km from the Jaisalmer Airport and 30 km from the Railway Station. Popular tourist attractions suchlike Jaisalmer Fort, Bada Bagh, Salim Singh Ki Haveli, The Thar Heritage Museum, Patwon Ki Haveli, Gadsisar Lake, Khaba Fort and many others are situated at a feasible distance from the hotel. Amidst the most beautiful landscapes and elegant interiors, the property features various modern facilities like travel desk, power backup, doctor on call, laundry, front desk, housekeeping and parking. Featuring capacious and spotlessly clean tents equipped with modern conveniences such as air conditioning, tea/coffee maker, desk and attached bathrooms with hot/cold water and essential toiletries. The property features an on site dining venue serving regional and continental delights that will surely pamper the taste buds of guests. Moreover, it offers various recreational activities like folk dance performances, camp fire and safari tours and many other entertaining events are organised for the guests. Desert Safariors Camps is an oasis of peace and tranquillity!', 6148, 5.0, 4.0, 5.0),
(3077, 318, 'Nomads Guest House', 'Fort Rd, Amar Sagar Pol, Jaisalmer', 'Nomads Guest House is located in Jaisalmer and boasts the grandeur and splendor of the royal era of Rajasthan. It is 3.1 km from Jaisalmer Airport, 2 km from Railway Station and 3.2 km from bus stand. The historical importance of Jaisalmer has played a vital role in elevating the status of Rajasthan as a tourist destination. Some of the prominent places are Jaisalmer Fort (170 m), Salim Singh Ki Haveli (800 m), Gadsisar Lake (1.7 km) and Bada Bagh (7.6 km). The property is decorated with elements that keeps the former elegance intact. Quietly elegant and exclusive the guest house facilitates like WiFi, parking, room service, luggage storage, laundry service, transportation and other recreational activities like desert trip, jeep tour and camel safari. It offers rooms adorned with stylish fittings and are spacious and provided with a range of amenities and attached bathroom with hot/cold water and various other essential bathroom toiletries. The guest house boasts of an open air restaurant offering a wide variety of culinary delights and a tempting array of scrumptious delicacies at the on-site restaurant. A modern and contemporary space which has the essence of Jaisalmer wonderfully woven in Nomads Guest House!', 7937, 4.0, 4.0, 5.0),
(3078, 318, 'The Golden House', '28 CVS Colony Opposite Collectorate Hanuman Circle', 'Tucked away in The Sun City, a shimmering mirage in the Thar desert, Jaisalmer. The Golden House features state of the art facilities wrapped with reliable services in compassionate environment. The hotel is situated at the distance of 1 km from Rajasthan Parivahan Nigam Bus Stand and 3 km from Jaisalmer Railway Station. The nearest airport to the region is Jodhpur Airport. While relaxing at the property, guests can visit famous sightseeing places like Jaisalmer Fort (900 m), Patwon Ki Haveli (1 km), Salim Singh Ki Haveli (1 km), Gadisar Lake (3 km), Bada Bag (11 km) and many more. Shoppers can have fun filled shopping experience at nearby shopping mall. The hotel offers front desk, laundry, room service, WiFi, taxi car rental, travel assistance and other standard facilities. Guest can enjoy delicious and mouthwatering cuisines at in-house restaurant to pamper their taste buds. To discover the charm of desert visitors can avail the services of jeep and camel safari. The rooms are designed for comfort and are equipped with work area keeping in mind the needs of the modern traveler. They have evocative decor that combines old and new world charm and offers hassle-free stay to patrons. They are equipped with comfortable beds, exquisite linens, air-conditioner, telephones and many more. The guestrooms have modern bathrooms with supply of hot and cold water facility. Have a nice stay at the Golden House!', 9983, 4.0, 5.0, 5.0),
(3079, 318, 'Mool Raj Sagar', 'Mool Raj Sagar, A royal Jodhpur Camp,Sam Road Sam Road', 'Mool Raj Sagar - A Royal Jodhpur Camp, is located in the close proximity to various tourist places like Jaisalmer Fort, Bada Bagh, Patwon-Ki-Haveli, Sam Sand Dunes and Gadisar Lake. The hotel is located on Sam Road, and is approximately 300 km from the Jodhpur Airport, and 9 km from the Jaisalmer Railway Station. The hotel offers a range of facilities and services to its guests, including: swimming pool, lawns/gardens, yoga/meditation facilities on request, laundry services, doctor on call, taxi services, parking facility, and bonfire arrangement. The on request services provided by the hotel include airport/railway station transfer, sightseeing, guide service, outdoor activities, bicycles on hire, and ayurveda/massage facilities. Mool Raj Sagar can also provide banquet/tented conference facilities for up to 500 persons, and also accepts major credit cards. The 18 Royal Tents are comfortable and complete with modern amenities. In-room amenities include: mineral water, balcony/sit out, study table, room heater, and an attached wash room with hot/cold running water and bathroom toiletries. Rooms service is also available. The hotel houses an excellent multi-cuisine restaurant called Royal Jodhpur Tented Restaurant that serves a wide variety of delicious and wholesome dishes in Rajasthani, Indian and Continental cuisines. Mool Raj Sagar - A Royal Jodhpur Camp, a luxury tented property, offers visitors to beautiful Jaisalmer an opportunity to enjoy its stunning desert scenery and environment to the fullest.', 8328, 5.0, 5.0, 5.0),
